subject: RE: [junit] How to start with Junit
msgSnippet: Hi, Make sure that the u have JDK in ur classpath and path. U don t need to change anything to make the sample that comes with JUnit to work. The sample works.
messageBody:
Hi,
Make sure that the u have JDK in ur classpath and path. U don't need to
change anything to make the sample
that comes with JUnit to work. The sample works.

Cheers,
Dhar

-----Original Message-----
From: arathi.bhaskar@... [mailto:arathi.bhaskar@...]
Sent: Wednesday, January 23, 2002 2:49 PM
To: junit@yahoogroups.com
Subject: [junit] How to start with Junit


Hi

I want to know about Junit by working on that & see how it can be used in
our organization. I downloaded the package from www.junit.org , but it does
not seem to be complete.

Can anyone of you give me information on how do I get started. I have the
other materials & some idea based on which I can proceed once I get
started.

Thanks & Regards
Arathi
